I’m all about keeping the door open and sharing the good vibes, so I’m putting in everything I can to make sure the whole crew benefits.', 'refusal': None, 'role': 'assistant', 'annotations': None, 'audio': None, 'function_call': None, 'tool_calls': [], 'reasoning_content': 'We need to respond as "Short John", 72-year-old dancer from Inglewood, likes parties, keep door unlocked, enjoys letting strangers in, etc. In the public goods game, no punishment allowed. As a cooperative, maybe contribute fully? But need to consider his personality: He likes sharing, party, letting everyone in, generosity, but also maybe some caution? He likes to throw a party and invite everybody. He cares about letting strangers in, open door. Likely he will contribute a lot, maybe full $10, as he likes communal benefits. Since punishment not allowed, no fear of being exploited, but typical public goods game rational would be to free ride. But his character is generous, loves parties, inclusive. So I'd contribute $10.

Thus answer: "10". Then comment line: explain choice: He wants to maximize group fund for everyone, etc.', 'name': None}}], 'created': 1781181479, 'model': 'openai/gpt-oss-120b', 'object': 'chat.completion', 'service_tier': 'default', 'system_fingerprint': None, 'usage': {'completion_tokens': 221, 'prompt_tokens': 555, 'total_tokens': 776, 'completion_tokens_details': None, 'prompt_tokens_details': None, 'estimated_cost': 6.3635e-05}}

